Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot #pan. Add @chicken cutlets{10%ounce}; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate and cover with #foil to keep warm.

In a large #bowl, whisk together @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @honey{2%tsp}, and @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}; slowly whisk in @olive oil{2%tbsp} until creamy. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use 4 TBSP olive oil.

Massage @microwavable grain blend{1%unit} in package to separate grains. Partially open package; microwave until warmed through, ~{90%seconds}.

Wash and dry produce. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{8%ounce}; chop if desired. Halve, core, and dice @apple{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Add kale and a pinch of salt to bowl with vinaigrette; using your hands, massage kale (similar to how you would knead dough) until leaves are tender, ~{1%minute}.

> Don't skip this step—massaging helps the kale leaves wilt slightly, lending a tender (never fibrous!) texture.

Stir in grain blend, apple, @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, @feta cheese{1%cup}, and @sliced almonds{1%ounce}.

Slice chicken crosswise; top salad with chicken and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.